OL,3,CInfected Blood Scandal: Man would
OL,4,Crather have 'a healthy life' than money
OL,6,FA man from Workington who was infected
OL,7,Fwith contaminated blood while
OL,8,Freceiving treatment for leukaemia said
OL,9,F"most people would much rather have a
OL,10,Fhealthy life than the money" as the
OL,11,Fgovernment announce compensation to
OL,12,Fvictims.
OL,14,FStuart Hall contracted Hepatitis C
OL,15,Fwhen being treated for cancer as a
OL,16,Fteenager.
OL,18,FSpeaking to ITV Border, he reacted to
OL,19,Fthe announcement that all "infected or
OL,20,Faffected" by the contaminated blood
OL,21,Fscandal before the end of the year.
