OL,6,F"Julie has been going through this
OL,7,Fwith me since 1995 and she's been to
OL,8,Fall the appointments with me. She's
OL,9,Flived with it knowing how serious it
OL,10,Fcould be. She's been through it as
OL,11,Fmuch as I have to a degree."
OL,13,FLast year, it was recommended that the
OL,14,Fcompensation scheme should be set up
OL,15,Fto coincide with the completion of the
OL,16,Fpublic inquiry to ensure that victims
OL,17,Fwould be paid as quickly as possible,
OL,18,Fwhich never happened.
OL,20,FMr Hall believes the government "were
OL,21,Ftrying to avoid a huge bill".
